   <h1>RE: [VB] DblDoor Sunroof Barndoor Panel-RANT</h1>
   <b>Ronnie Feitelson &lt;Ronnie_at_OldVolks_dot_com&gt;</b><br/>
   <i>2001-03-22 23:47:58+00</i><br/>
   <br/>
   <pre>Well according to the general consensus of those that have responded on the
list to the Kustom Panel, sounds like Binz is a hack, being that it isn't VW
made, just some aftermarket company hacking a bus into something it wasn't
meant to be. The same must go for the bestalwagon (spelling) another
aftermarket thing. Everybody has there taste, wants and  feelings,
expressions etc. Most people think there buses are priceless, I do of my DD,
but to chastiz a person for doing something they enjoy, ripping on them for
asking such a high price, would you give your stuff away, or would you try
to get what YOU feel it is worth, not what the "MARKET" dictates. If you
want something bad enough you'll pay whatever it takes. I just had a
conversation with a good friend (owns a body shop) about prices. I need a
door for the new/old diesel Ford bus hauler I just bought. $88.00 dollars
for a Taiwan door shell, $145.00 for a better repo and $250.00 from F#rd or
$150.00 for used. Then I thought to myself about the bitching people do when
they have to pay $100.00 dollars for an absolutly MINT pre 62 bus door,
that's a perfect 40 plus year old door! where's the logic. This logic people
use always seems to get to me. What qualifies a Kustom, reconditioned,
restored, perfect restoration, 100% original, driver, show bus. Somebody
please lay down the rules!! I guess Kelly Park will be the defining factor
to this question by what they will allow and won't into the show. I'd hate
to be the person deciding if a bus is custom or not. Thom's panel is a
custom, isn't it. Bright yellow paint, filled in back window, tent, none of
this original to the bus. So according to what most people are saying,
anything none stock would be classified a custom, if it isn't pure stock,
i.e.; engine, trans, tires, etc. Let everybody be themselves, enjoying there
buses and helping the hobby grow, regardless of your or my likes and
dislikes. 

ronnie   major fire suit on/flame red bus coming soon

-----Original Message-----
From: Thom Fitzpatrick [mailto:thom_at_calweb_dot_com]
Sent: Thursday, March 22, 2001 1:01 PM
To: vintagebus_at_type2_dot_com
Subject: Re: [VB] DblDoor Sunroof Barndoor Panel-RANT


I can't resist a good street fight, so I'll wade into the fray.

As I've said before, the problem with doing a kustom kar - 
irrespective of how meticulous the craftsmanship - is that
to sell it, you have to find someone with almost the exact
tastes.   Do your car the way *you* want to, to make yourself
happy.  When the time comes to sell, you have the choice of
sucking up and taking the loss, or holding out until you get
the right buyer, or a combination of the two.  Flak is inevitable.
Even if you had a perfectly OG, 100 pt concours '51 deluxe for
sale, *someone* is going to shovel a ration your way for 
some particular reason.</pre>


